<p>Despite the rudeness of this “graffiti”, we are sure its creator has been through A LOT before reaching the point of no return. </p>
<p>While we wait for modern parking systems to solve the stress that this entails on citizens, we sure hope Lebanese citizens <strong>keep on getting creative</strong>, but <strong>a tiny bit less insulting</strong>, when venting.</p>";s:17:"post_image_height";i:698;s:16:"post_image_width";i:489;s:11:"post_visits";i:7;s:18:"post_twitterShares";i:0;s:19:"post_facebookShares";i:19;s:16:"post_totalShares";i:19;s:16:"post_socialScore";i:19;s:13:"post_virality";i:24;s:9:"blog_name";s:16:"Blog of the Boss";s:16:"blog_description";s:68:"Strong believer in social change and in the healing power of comedy.";s:8:"blog_url";s:25:"http://blogoftheboss.com/";s:11:"blog_author";s:10:"Ralph Aoun";s:28:"blog_author_twitter_username";s:9:"ralphaoun";s:13:"blog_rss_feed";s:30:"http://blogoftheboss.com/feed/";s:9:"blog_tags";s:17:"politics, society";s:2:"id";i:287;s:11:"blog_active";i:1;s:24:"blog_last_post_timestamp";i:1401669000;}i:3;O:8:"stdClass":26:{s:7:"post_id";i:30068;s:8:"post_url";s:81:"http://sharbelfaraj.wordpress.com/2014/05/23/lebanons-new-3g-dsl-and-calls-rates/";s:10:"post_title";s:39:"Lebanon’s new 3G, DSL and calls rates";s:10:"post_image";s:55:"http://sharbelfaraj.files.wordpress.com/2014/05/dsl.jpg";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:123:"Cell calls:- For prepaid plans: 0.25$/1min and 0.05$/1sms- Postpaid customers will get 60 free minutes (for the reason o...";s:7:"blog_id";s:12:"sharbelfaraj";s:14:"post_timestamp";i:1400832300;s:12:"post_content";s:1172:"<p><strong>Cell calls:</strong><br>- For prepaid plans: 0.25$/1min and 0.05$/1sms<br>- Postpaid customers will get 60 free minutes (for the reason of paying 15$ monthly and getting no services for).<br>- Postpaid lines won’t require a $25/month connection fee.</p>
<p><strong>3G:</strong><br><em>WILL BE UPDATED</em></p>
<p><strong>Landlines:<br></strong>- Citizens will be able to get a landline without paying any fee of incorporation.<br>- Monthly fee reduced from 12,000 LBP to 9,000 LBP.</p>
<p><strong>DSL:<br></strong><a href="http://sharbelfaraj.files.wordpress.com/2014/05/dsl.jpg"><img src="http://sharbelfaraj.files.wordpress.com/2014/05/dsl.jpg?w=455" alt="Image"></a></p>
<p><span><strong>P.S:</strong></span><strong> </strong>New rates will be applied starting July 1st.</p><br><a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/gocomments/sharbelfaraj.wordpress.com/1635/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/comments/sharbelfaraj.wordpress.com/1635/"></a> <img alt="" border="0" src="http://stats.wordpress.com/b.gif?host=sharbelfaraj.wordpress.com&blog=34529022&post=1635&subd=sharbelfaraj&ref=&feed=1" width="1" height="1">";s:17:"post_image_height";i:299;s:16:"post_image_width";i:465;s:11:"post_visits";i:21;s:18:"post_twitterShares";i:8;s:19:"post_facebookShares";i:20;s:16:"post_totalShares";i:28;s:16:"post_socialScore";i:35;s:13:"post_virality";i:27;s:9:"blog_name";s:13:"Sharbel Faraj";s:16:"blog_description";s:41:"Spreading Culture & Awareness | Since '96";s:8:"blog_url";s:34:"http://sharbelfaraj.wordpress.com/";s:11:"blog_author";s:13:"Sharbel Faraj";s:28:"blog_author_twitter_username";s:12:"sharbelfaraj";s:13:"blog_rss_feed";s:39:"http://sharbelfaraj.wordpress.com/feed/";s:9:"blog_tags";s:17:"politics, society";s:2:"id";i:275;s:11:"blog_active";i:1;s:24:"blog_last_post_timestamp";i:1401461760;}i:4;O:8:"stdClass":26:{s:7:"post_id";i:30059;s:8:"post_url";s:69:"http://stateofmind13.com/2014/05/23/lebanons-new-3g-dsl-phone-prices/";s:10:"post_title";s:38:"Lebanon’s New 3G, DSL & Phone Prices";s:10:"post_image";s:78:"https://stateofmind13.files.wordpress.com/2014/05/20140523-100726-36446509.jpg";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:123:"I was invited today to the press conference that’s announcing the new tariffs for Lebanon’s upcoming telecom upgrade...";s:7:"blog_id";s:13:"stateofmind13";s:14:"post_timestamp";i:1400829000;s:12:"post_content";s:2819:"<p><a href="https://stateofmind13.files.wordpress.com/2014/05/20140523-100726-36446509.jpg"><img src="https://stateofmind13.files.wordpress.com/2014/05/20140523-100726-36446509.jpg?w=620" alt="20140523-100726-36446509.jpg"></a></p>
<p>I was invited today to the press conference that’s announcing the new tariffs for Lebanon’s upcoming telecom upgrades.</p>
<p><strong>Pre-Conference Tidbits:</strong></p>
<p>At the Ministry of Telecommunications is now various posters to hint at the upgrades which will be announced in a few. So as a first taste, find the following picture:</p>
<p><a href="https://stateofmind13.files.wordpress.com/2014/05/20140523-100918-36558902.jpg"><img src="https://stateofmind13.files.wordpress.com/2014/05/20140523-100918-36558902.jpg?w=620" alt="20140523-100918-36558902.jpg"></a></p>
<p>So what we know so far is the following:<br>
- We will have unlimited internet bundles,<br>
- Postpaid lines won’t require a $25 per month connection fee,<br>
- Speeds are to be doubled.</p>
